
Overview of verb pare

The verb pare has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) pare, pare down -- (decrease gradually or bit by bit)
2. whittle, pare -- (cut small bits or pare shavings from; "whittle a piece of wood")
3. skin, peel, pare -- (strip the skin off; "pare apples")
4. pare, trim -- (remove the edges from and cut down to the desired size; "pare one's fingernails"; "trim the photograph"; "trim lumber")
